The Energy Department says the fuel price will drop from midnight on Tuesday. All grades of petrol will drop by 13 cents a litre, diesel by 14 cents and 16 cents while paraffin will drop by 31 cents a litre. Department of Energy spokesperson Robert Maake says the main reason for the drop in fuel prices is the drop in crude oil prices. Listen for more: <a href="https://iono.fm/e/766384">Content hosted by iono.fm</a>